		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sure, if you beat one version fast enough, you get <a href="http://www.thisischris.com/feature/2005/samus.html" class="postlink">Ms. Aran in a bikini</a>. But what kind of completion time did you get in order to get the bikini to disappear?</div><br />I don't know how long it took. It was done with a "perfect run" password from the "Metroid Password Generator": Start in Tourian, all items collected and even Mother Brain defeated (yes, it's possible to choose that in the Password Generator, so you can just pass and don't have to fight her), but the clock still at 0 seconds when starting to play. (So, it's a password that you could never get during normal gameplay.) And then go straight through Tourian and don't lose any unnecessary time. And bam: Nude Samus. Probably a little gag by the programmers since they knew that no-one would ever find it out. Well, they didn't think of emulators.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A mod should change the original message to read that he found secret worlds in Metroid (the ones that have been known about for ages), along with screenshots showing these "new" discoveries.</div><br />I never claimed to have found a new world. Except of course, if with "new world" you refer to Samus' vajayjay.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">At least JohnJohn's nudity fixation has become NES-related this time. But be very careful, JohnJohn: I brought my banhammer. If you can't give a good reason behind this post, I have no choice but to declare you unconstructive.</div>
